INTERNATIONAL PARASITOLOGY CONGRESS, CUBA, 17-23 NOVEMBER 1997
==============================================================
From: ciipk <ciipk@ipk.sld.cu>
Date: Wed, 21 May 1997 15:49:12 +-100
XIII Latin American Congress of Parasitology

"PREVENTION AND CONTROL OF PARASITOSIS IN LATIN AMERICA"
Institute of Tropical Medicine "Pedro Koured", La Habana, Cuba. 17-23
November 1997
Scientific Program:
Activities will include: pre-congress courses, state of the art lectures,
workshops, symposia and posters, oral and informal sessions on subjects
relevant to the prevention and control of parasitic diseases of medical,
veterinary, plant and marine importance. Simultaneous Spanish-English and
English-Spanish translation will be available during the plenary sessions
and the main state of the art lectures.
Some items of special interest at the congress include: Hemo and intestinal
parasites, vectors and Intermediate hosts, vaccine development, diagnostic
procedures, ectoparasites, therapeutics, epidemiology, molecular biology,
social and economic research and multicenter projects with relevance within
the theme of the congress.
Abstract submission and Deadline
Abstracts must be submitted in Spanish on the enclosed ABSTRACT FORM. Once
accepted the abstracts will be published using a directed reproduction, so
that they will appear exactly as they were typed. The authors are requested
to type the abstract according to the instructions given in the ABSTRACT
FORM. The deadline for receiving the ABSTRACT FORM is 27 July, 1997. It must
be sent along with the REGISTRATION FORM to the congress secretariat. At
least one of the authors must pay the registration fee when submitting the
abstract. The acceptance of the abstract will be notified by the congress
secretariat before 1 September 1997.
More information could be obtained from:
Dr. Carlos M Finlay, President of the Organizing Committee,
Instituto "Pedro Koured" (IPK)
Apartado 601, Marianao 13,
Ciudad de la Habana,
Cuba
Phone: (53-7)-218042=20
Fax: (53-7)-336051
(53-7)-215957
e-mail: ciipk@ipk.sld.cu
